sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Notebook Pod
    participant Gateway as Gateway HTTPRoute<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant MLflow as MLflow Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant DB as PostgreSQL Database<br/>5432/TCP TLS1.2+ (optional)
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Experiment Tracking from Notebook

    User->>MLflow: POST /api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/create<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Auth approved
    MLflow->>DB: INSERT experiment metadata<br/>Password auth
    DB-->>MLflow: Success
    MLflow->>S3: PUT /artifacts/experiment.pkl<br/>AWS credentials
    S3-->>MLflow: Artifact stored
    MLflow-->>User: Experiment created (JSON)

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: MLflow CR Creation & Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f mlflow.yaml<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (MLflow CR created)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service + annotation<br/>service.beta.openshift.io/serving-cert-secret-name
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PVC<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConsoleLink<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over K8sAPI,ServiceCA: OpenShift service-ca watches Service
    ServiceCA->>K8sAPI: Create mlflow-tls Secret<br/>TLS cert/key

    MLflow->>DB: Initialize schema<br/>CREATE TABLE experiments
    DB-->>MLflow: Schema ready
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: Pod ready signal

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Web UI Access via Gateway

    User->>Gateway: GET /<br/>Session Cookie
    Gateway->>MLflow: Forward request<br/>Bearer Token
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Auth approved
    MLflow->>DB: SELECT experiments<br/>Password auth
    DB-->>MLflow: Experiment list
    MLflow-->>Gateway: HTML response
    Gateway-->>User: MLflow Web UI
